🚀 **Day 10 of My AI/ML Journey — Accuracy, Precision, Recall & F1 Score**

Hey everyone 👋
Welcome to **Day 10**! Today I learned how to **measure the performance of classification models** 🔥

👉 Just accuracy is NOT enough… we need deeper metrics!

---

## 📌 What I Learned Today

### 🔹 1. Accuracy

* Percentage of correct predictions

👉 Formula:

* (Correct Predictions) / (Total Predictions)

💡 Works well only when data is balanced

---

### 🔹 2. Precision

* Out of all predicted positives, how many were actually correct?

👉 Focus: **Avoid false positives**

💡 Example:
Spam detection — don’t mark important emails as spam

---

### 🔹 3. Recall

* Out of all actual positives, how many did we correctly identify?

👉 Focus: **Avoid false negatives**

💡 Example:
Disease detection — don’t miss actual patients

---

### 🔹 4. F1 Score

* Balance between Precision & Recall

👉 Used when both are important

---

## 🔥 Simple Understanding

* Accuracy → Overall correctness
* Precision → “How correct when I say YES?”
* Recall → “Did I miss any YES?”
* F1 → Balance ⚖️

💡 **Memory Trick:**
👉 *Precision = Quality | Recall = Coverage*

---

## 🧠 Key Takeaways

* Accuracy alone can be misleading
* Precision & Recall are crucial in real-world problems
* F1 score helps balance both

